cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper deals with attention mechanisms in computer vision, specifically in the context of single image super-resolution. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new residual attention module, which falls under the category of deep learning and neural networks, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely categories as well. The paper also involves optimization of the attention mechanisms, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
